            <h4>How to get there</h4>
            <p>
                In Manila, Victory Liner, Five Star and Philippine Rabbit bus lines have daily trips bound for Alaminos City which traverse the provinces of Bulacan, Pampanga and Tarlac. The esti- mated travel time is five to six hours.
            </p>
            <p>
                From Baguio City, there are trips that go straight to Ala- minos or one can take a bus to Dagupan City and easily transfer to one that is bound Alaminos. The estimated travel time is two to three hours. There is also a domestic airport in San Fernando City, La Union and public buses have trips to Alaminos via Dagupan City. The estimated travel time from Dagupan to Alaminos is one to two hours.
            </p>

            <h4>Best time to visit</h4>
            <p>
                April and May are the best months to spend time in Alaminos City and in the Hundred Islands. There is less chance of rain and visitors are assured of hot summer days and balmy nights.
            </p>

